attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is a private application by Halcyon Management Group requesting a phased implementation certification pursuant to ZR 62-811 and substantial compliance of the previously approved waterfront certification (N 150371ZCK) to facilitate a mixed-use development at 27-41 West Street, Greenpoint, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

This is a private application by Heritage Equities requesting a zoning map amendment and large scale general development plan to facilitate a new 360,000 square foot commercial development at 215 Moore Street in East Williamsburg, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

An application by the DSNY for acquisition of an open parking lot at 145 Randolph Street to facilitate the continued use of the site as Community district 3 sanitation parking lot, located in East Williamsburg, Community District 1, Brooklyn.
attributes.actiontypes: Acquisition of Property by the City

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Application by the DSNY for acquisition of a property at 525 Johnson Avenue to facilitate the continued use of the  site as Community District 3 Sanitation Garage located in eastern Williamsburg, Community District 1, Brooklyn.
attributes.actiontypes: Acquisition of Property by the City

attributes.dcp_projectname: POPS Signage and Amenities Text Amendment
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: The New York City Department of City Planning (DCP) proposes an amendment to update certain provisions of the Zoning Resolution related to signage and amenities in privately owned public spaces (POPS). The proposed text amendment would facilitate the updating of the existing public space symbol; require public space signage for various types of POPS; and permit publicly accessible moveable tables and chairs to be placed in plazas and arcades where they are currently prohibited.

This is a private application by Waterview at Greenpoint LLC, pursuant to Section 11-43 ZR requesting a renewal of a special permit (C 140047 ZSK) for a three year term, and renewal of two authorizations (N 140048 ZAK and N 140049 ZAK) to facilitate the development of 720 units of housing, including 200 affordable units, and ground floor retail, located within three 30- to 40-story buildings at 77 Commercial Street in Greenpoint, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

This is a private application by 12 Franklin Property Co LLC, 12 Franklin 230 LLC and 12 Franklin 197 LLC requesting a Zoning Text Amendment and Zoning Special Permits pursuant to Section 74-96 to facilitate a new seven-story, approximately 134,222 square foot mixed office, retail,and industrial  building at 12 Franklin Street, Greenpoint, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

This is a private application by the Rabsky Group requesting a zoning text amendment and special permits pursuant to Section 74-96 to facilitate a new 7-story, 60,000 sf commercial/industrial building in Williamsburg, Community District 1, Brooklyn.
This is a private application to renew authorizations (ZR 11-42, ZR 11-43) pursuant to ZR Sections 62-822(a) and 62-822(b) in the Greenpoint neighborhood of Brooklyn Community District 1.

This is a private application by Spitzer Enterprises requesting an authorization Pursuant to ZR 62-822 (c) for a Waterfront Public Access Area Phasing Plan for a mixed-use development at 420 Kent Avenue, in Williamsburg, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

attributes.dcp_projectname: Greenpoint Landing Parcel 5C - Waterfront ZC, ZA

attributes.applicants: GREENPOINT LANDING ASSOCIATES, LLC;GREENPOINT LANDING ASSOCIATES LLC

attributes.dcp_projectname: The Dime Savings Bank of Williamsburgh
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: This is an application by the Landmarks Preservation Commission to facilitate the designation of The Dime Savings Bank of Williamsburgh as a Landmark,  at 209 Havemeyer Street in Williamsburg, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

(ULURP # N 180476 ECK) Renewal application by Fortunato Bros. Cafe & Bakery Corp.. d/b/a, Fortunato Bros., for a revocable consent to operare an existing enclosed sidewalk cafe with 14 tables and 48 seats at 189 Mahattan Avenue on the northwest corner of Devoe Street.

This is a private application by Martin Kofman, American Package Co, Inc. to request a Chair's Certification pursuant to Zoning Resolution Section 15-30(b) to modify the open space equivalent requirements of ZR Sec. 15-12 in connection with a residential conversion at 226 Franklin Street, Brooklyn Community District 1.
attributes.applicants: Martin Kofman;MARTIN KOFMAN AMERICAN PACKAGE CO INC

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: A private application proposing a zoning map amendment to facilitate change of use and enlargement of first floor, affecting the west blockfront of Bedford Avenue from N 10 St to N 11 St: the zoning map amendment would extend a C1-4 overlay to an existing R6A district, in Williamsburg, Community District 1, Brooklyn.

Zoning text amendment to subject as-of-right self-storage development within Designated Areas in M districts, which largely coincide with Industrial Business Zones, to certain conditions, and to establish a CPC Special Permit under the jurisdiction of the City Planning Commission in order to modify or waive such conditions.

This is a private application by Harrison Realty LLC for land use actions to facilitate the development of eight buildings comprising 859 market rate and 287 affordable dwelling units, and approximately 63,000 square feet of retail located on two blocks in the South Williamsburg section of Brooklyn, Community District 1.

Zoning {62-822(b)} authorization to modify planting requirements within a previously approved Waterfront Public Access Area  to facilitate artificial turf on flexible field (SPAA 3), and a new zoning {62-811} certification to verify compliance with Zoning waterfront regulations in Brooklyn Community District 1, Williamsburg.
attributes.applicants: DOMINO A LLC AND DOMINO B LLC;Laura Cheng

attributes.dcp_projectbrief: Second special permit renewal application pursuant to ZR Sec. 11-43 and an Authorization renewal for Rose Plaza on the River development in the South Williamsburg neighborhood of Brooklyn Community District 1.

This is a private application for a text amendment pursuant to Section 62-35 of the Zoning Resolution to reorient the massing of a proposed 11-story mixed use building towards a public park (Transmitter Park) in the Greenpoint neighborhood of Brooklyn, Community District 1
The Landmarks Preservation Commission is requesting a report from the City Planning Commission on the landmark designation of 183-195 Broadway (LP-1504) in Brooklyn, Community District 1.

attributes.dcp_projectname: 420 Kent Ave - Kedem Winery Waterfront Cert
attributes.dcp_projectbrief: A private application for a zoning certification by the Chairperson that a proposed development meets the regulations of Article 6 Chapter 2 (in regards to the provision of waterfront public access areas and visual corridors ) of the zoning resolution in Brooklyn Community District 1.

An application by the Department of Environmental Protection for a site selection and City Map amendment to facilitate the 3rd phase of development of a nature walk in conjunction with the Newtown Creek Wastewater Treatment Plant Upgrade in the Greenpoint neighborhood of Brooklyn, Community District 1.

These are applications by EDC for Zoning Certifications (ZC) to allow docking facilities for ferries or water taxis, increase the capacity of vessels and the provide amenities as delineated in the Waterfront Access Plan, at these sites: Shaefer/S.Williamsburg, India Street/Greenpoint, N6th Street) in Brooklyn Community District 1.

The applicant, Heritage Equity, is seeking a Zoning Text Amendment and two Special Permits 74-962 and 74-963, pursuant to the new text, in order to facilitate the development of a 380,000 square foot mixed office, retail, and light industrial building in the northern Williamsburg neighborhood of Brooklyn, Community District 1.
